The House of Representatives passed abill that requires financial institutions to disclose the termsand conditions of interest rates they offer on savingsaccounts.    Institutions would be required to disclose throughadvertisments and announcements the minimum balances, timerequirements, fees and other conditions of their savingsaccounts, certificates of deposits and interest-bearingchecking accounts.       The purpose of the bill is to help customers decide whichbanks and savings associations offer the best rates, accordingto House Banking Committee chairman Fernand St Germain, a RhodeIsland Democrat.    The bill was passed by voice vote and sent to the Senate. Reuter&#3;